methods.fillChunk:
Populates the given destination chunk with data corresponding to the keys from the given OrderedKeys.

:param context: (io.deephaven.db.v2.sources.chunk.ChunkSource.FillContext) - A context containing all mutable/state related data used in retrieving the Chunk.
:param destination: (io.deephaven.db.v2.sources.chunk.WritableChunk<? superio.deephaven.db.v2.sources.chunk.Attributes.Values>) - The chunk to be populated according to orderedKeys. No assumptions shall be made about
        the size of the chunk shall be made. The chunk will be populated from position [0,orderedKeys.size()).
:param orderedKeys: (io.deephaven.db.v2.utils.OrderedKeys) - An OrderedKeys representing the keys to be fetched

methods.getUngrouped:
Reach into a grouped column source and pull one element out of the array.

:param groupIndexKey: (long) - the index within the column of the cell to get
:param offsetInGroup: (int) - the index within the array at the specified cell
:return: (java.lang.Object) Equivalent to ((DbArray)columnSource.get(columnIndex)).get(arrayIndex)
methods.getUngroupedSize:
:param groupIndexKey: (long) - the index within this column to interrogate
:return: (long) the size of the DbArray at columnIndex.
methods.isUngroupable:
Does this particular instance of the column source support ungrouping?

:return: (boolean) true if you can call the getUngrouped family of methods and get a valid answer.
methods.makeFillContext:
Allocate a new ChunkSource.FillContext for filling chunks from this FillContextMaker, typically a
 ChunkSource.

:param chunkCapacity: (int) - The maximum size of any WritableChunk that will be filled with this context
:param sharedContext: (io.deephaven.db.v2.sources.chunk.SharedContext) - Shared store of intermediate results.
:return: (io.deephaven.db.v2.sources.chunk.ChunkSource.FillContext) A context for use with fill operations
methods.startTrackingPrevValues:
ColumnSource implementations that track previous values have the option to not actually start tracking previous
 values until this method is called. This is an option, not an obligation: some simple ColumnSource
 implementations (like TSingleValueSource for various T) always track previous values; other implementations (like
 PrevColumnSource) never do; some (like TArrayColumnSource) only start tracking once this method is called.

 An immutable column source can not have distinct prev values; therefore it is implemented as a no-op.

text: ColumnSource implementation for aggregation result long columns.
